gomodel:SYNGO_371  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The paper shows that in KO mice for gephyrin synaptic localization of GABA(A) receptors is impaired.\n\n29/3/2017 Pim\n- The clustering of GABARs is shown to be at synapses in Fig.3 via colocalization of the presynaptic marker synaptophysin.\n- The \"regulation ...\" box is not checked because gephyrin is a scaffolding protein.. Experimental description: The creation and phenotype of geph / mice have been described previously (Feng et al., 1998) p. 9290." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" ;
        dc:date           "2017-03-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_371" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

